{
  "text": "Definition 8.2 (see [CITATION_1] ). Let C be a left H-module coalgebra, (\u0398,D) be a left DGH-module coalgebra and M be a right-left SAYD module over H. An n-dimensional \u0398-cycle over C is a tuple (\u0398,D,x, \u033a) wherex is an n-dimensional closed graded (H, M )-cotrace on \u0398 and \u033a \u2236 \u0398 0 \u2192 C is an H-linear coalgebra map.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "125764059"
